LATIN AMERICA AND CANADA AREA SALES BY 7.4%, AND THE ASIA PACIFIC AREA SALES BY

0.5%, AS THE U.S. DOLLAR WEAKENED AGAINST THESE CURRENCIES. FOREIGN CURRENCY

TRANSLATION HAD A MINIMAL IMPACT ON EUROPEAN SALES.

