REFER TO ADDITIONAL DISCUSSION LATER IN NOTE 1 CONCERNING THE IMPACT OF SFAS

NO. 123R SHARE BASED PAYMENT. PRO FORMA AMOUNTS FOR STOCK OPTION AWARDS ARE

BASED ON THE OPTIONS ESTIMATED BLACK-SCHOLES FAIR VALUE AT THE DATE OF GRANT,

NET OF TAX, WITH EXPENSE RECOGNITION OVER THE VESTING PERIOD OF THE STOCK-BASED

COMPENSATION AWARD.  EFFECTIVE WITH THE

MAY 2005 ANNUAL MSOP GRANT, THE COMPANY CHANGED ITS VESTING PERIOD FROM ONE TO

THREE YEARS, WHICH RESULTS IN COMPENSATION EXPENSE UNDER THE MAY 2005 ANNUAL

GRANT BEING RECOGNIZED OVER THREE YEARS. THE DECREASE IN PRO FORMA STOCK-BASED

COMPENSATION FOR 2005 COMPARED WITH 2004 WAS PRIMARILY DRIVEN BY THIS CHANGE IN

VESTING PERIOD. SHARES USED IN THE PRO FORMA DILUTED EARNINGS PER SHARE

COMPUTATION USE THE CALCULATION METHODOLOGY PRESCRIBED BY SFAS NO. 123,

AND ARE THUS DIFFERENT FROM THE SHARES USED FOR THE REPORTED DILUTED EARNINGS

PER SHARE COMPUTATION. PRO FORMA AMOUNTS FOR STOCK-BASED COMPENSATION ARE AS

