COURT GRANTED THE COMPANYS MOTION TO DISMISS THE CLAIMS FOR MEDICAL MONITORING

AND PUBLIC NUISANCE IN APRIL 2005, THE PLAINTIFFS FILED AN AMENDED COMPLAINT

ADDING ADDITIONAL ALLEGATIONS INVOLVING OTHER PERFLUORONATED COMPOUNDS

MANUFACTURED BY THE COMPANY, ALLEGING ADDITIONAL LEGAL THEORIES IN SUPPORT OF

THEIR

67

